Definition: being complete of its kind and without defect or blemish
Example: a perfect circle; a perfect reproduction; perfect happiness; perfect manners; a perfect specimen; a perfect day
Synonyms: IMPERFECT, EXACT, UNBLEMISHED, UNBROKEN, UTOPIAN, noun, state, perfection, being, complete, of, its, kind, and, without, defect, or, blemish, a, perfect, circle, reproduction, happiness, manners, specimen, day
Category: adj.all
